{
  "stem": "11274.1",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then she kept me for helping to do-- to-- to correct the homework from the smaller, the lower classes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then she and the other teachers arranged it that from other towns [INAUDIBLE] teachers came in and taught during the whole year for extended education.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I-- I had already studied the German, so I didn't take the German there if they were offering it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And also the subjects what you teach in extended education after grade school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But most of the children were just, just in grade, grade school education.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We, we didn't have an [INAUDIBLE] newspaper.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in Krynica-- as I said, seven kilometers from us, was a world-famous resort.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's Krynica.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were villas, there was all the luxury that-- that anybody can imagine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You could hear on the course while walking-- could hear five, six languages, foreign languages speaking.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "People from all over the world used to come to the mountains for the winter for skiing, and the summer for mineral baths they had there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [INAUDIBLE]-- so this was also part of the children when we were old enough, after grade school, to take a walk the seven kilometers to Krynica.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We could go to Krynica, and we could listen to famous singers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Jan Kiepura was a Polish famous singer, Marta Eggerth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You probably don't know the name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they were very little-known here in America, even though he died and lived the last years of his life-- when the Germans came, they escaped to America, he and his wife.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Marta Eggerth and-- both singers and-- so we would go to a famous singer like this one, Jan Kiepura.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
